n></span>, Mawdsley C, Adams R. On the pathogenesis of focal nodular hyperplasia of the liver. <em>Hepatology</em>1985; 5(6): 1194–2000.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1002/hep.1840050622">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/4065824/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Hepatology&amp;publication_year=1985&amp;pages=1194&amp;doi=10.1002%2Fhep.1840050622&amp;pmid=4065824">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">6.</div><div id="R6" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content"><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-firstauthor"><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-snm">Kamel</span><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-fnm">IR</span></span>, Liapi E, Fishman EK. Focal nodular hyperplasia: lesion evaluation using 16-MDCT and 3D CT angiography. <em>AJR Am J Roentgenol</em>2006; 186(6): 1587–1596.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.2214/AJR.05.0030">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/16714647/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=AJR+Am+J+Roentgenol&amp;publication_year=2006&amp;pages=1587&amp;doi=10.2214%2FAJR.05.0030&amp;pmid=16714647">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">7.</div><div id="R7" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content"><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-firstauthor"><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-snm">Brancatelli</span><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-fnm">G</span></span>, Federle MP, Grazioli L, Blachar A, Peterson MS, Thaete L. Focal nodular hyperplasia: CT findings with emphasis on multiphasic helical CT in 78 patients. <em>Radiology</em>2001; 219(1): 61–68.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1148/radiology.219.1.r01ap0361">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/11274535/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Radiology&amp;publication_year=2001&amp;pages=61&amp;doi=10.1148%2Fradiology.219.1.r01ap0361&amp;pmid=11274535">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">8.</div><div id="R8" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content"><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-firstauthor"><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-snm">Blachar</span><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-fnm">A</span></span>, Federle MP, Ferris JV, et al. Radiologists’ performance in the diagnosis of liver tumors with central scars by using specific CT criteria. <em>Radiology</em>2002; 223(2): 532–539.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1148/radiol.2232010801">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/11997564/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Radiology&amp;publication_year=2002&amp;pages=532&amp;doi=10.1148%2Fradiol.2232010801&amp;pmid=11997564">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">9.</div><div id="R9" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content"><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-firstauthor"><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-snm">Semelka</span><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-fnm">RC</span></span>, Martin DR, Balci C, Lance T. Focal live