<div class="core-journal-description"><div property="isPartOf" typeof="Periodical"><span property="name">RadioGraphics</span></div><div class="core-enumeration"><span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationVolume">Volume <span property="volumeNumber">29</span></span> • <span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationIssue">Number <span property="issueNumber">1</span></span> • <span property="datePublished">Jan 1 2009</span></div><div class="core-pagination"><span class="heading">Pages</span>: <span class="content"><span property="pageStart">211</span> - <span property="pageEnd">229</span></span></div><div class="core-pmid"><span class="heading">PubMed</span>: <a class="content" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/19168846/" property="sameAs" target="_blank" title="Link to PubMed">19168846</a></div></div></div></section><section class="core-copyright"><h4>Copyright</h4><div role="paragraph">© RSNA, 2009.</div></section><section class="core-history"><h4>History</h4><div><b class="core-label">Published online</b>: Jan 1 2009</div></section><section class="core-permissions"><h4>Permissions</h4><div>Request permissions for this article.</div><div><a class="btn" href="https://marketplace.copyright.com/rs-ui-web/mp/search/all/10.1148%2Frg.291085099">Request Permissions</a></div></section><section property="keywords"><h4>Keywords</h4><ol><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=FNH+%3D+focal+nodular+hyperplasia&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">FNH = focal nodular hyperplasia</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=HCC+%3D+hepatocellular+carcinoma&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">HCC = hepatocellular carcinoma</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=NRH+%3D+nodular+regenerative+hyperplasia&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">NRH = nodular regenerative hyperplasia</a></li></ol></section><section class="core-article-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="paragraph">Imaging features of common and uncommon benign hepatic tumors are reviewed according to their cell of origin, and the imaging appearances of iatrogenic pseudotumors of the liver are presented.</div></section></section><section id="tab-contributors" role="tabpanel"><h3>Authors</h3><section class="core-authors"><h4>Affiliations</h4><div id="con1" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Stephan W.</span> <span property="familyName">Anderson</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Department of Radiology, Beth Israel Deaconess Medical Center, 330 Brookline Ave, Boston, MA 02215. Presented as an education exhibit at the 2007 RSNA Annual Meeting. Received April 18, 2008; revision requested May 21; final revision received June 21; accepted June 27. All authors have no financial relationships to disclose.</span></div></div><div class="core-author-link"><a href="/authored-by/Anderson/Stephan+W" rel="nofollow">View all articles by this author</a></div></div></div><div id="con2" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Jonathan B.</span> <span property="familyName">Kruskal</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD, PhD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Department of Radiology, Beth Israel Deaconess Medical Center, 330 Brookline Ave, Boston, MA 02215. Presented as an education exhibit at the 2007 RSNA Annual Meeting. Received April 18, 2008; revision requested May 21; final revision received June 21; accepted June 27. All authors have no financial relationships to disclose.</span></div></div><div class="core-author-link"><a href="/authored-by/Kruskal/Jonathan+B" rel="nofollow">View all articles by this author</a></div></div></div><div id="con3" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Robert A.</span> <span property="familyName">Kane</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Department of Radiology, Beth Israel Deaconess Medical Center, 330 Brookline Ave, Boston, MA 02215. Presented as an education exhibit at the 2007 RSNA Annual Meeting. Received April 18, 2008; revision requested May 21; final revision received June 21; accepted June 27. All authors have no financial relationships to disclose.</span></div></div><div class="core-author-link"><a href="/authored-by/Kane/Robert+A" rel="nofollow">View all articles by this author</a></div></div></div></section><section class="core-authors-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="doc-footnote"><b>Address correspondence to</b> S.W.A. (e-mail: <i><a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#d8abacbda8b0b9b6f6b9b6bcbdaaabb7b698bab5bbf6b7aabf"><span class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="f7848392879f9699d99699939285849899b7959a94d9988590">[email&#160;protected]</span></a></i>).</div></section></section></div><div id="core-collateral-metrics" data-active-pane="false"><header><h2><i class="icon-timeline" aria-hidden="true"></i>Metrics &amp; Citations</h2></header><section id="tab-metrics-inner" role="tabpanel"><h3>Metrics</h3><section>



        
